'''Fang''' (b. circa [[1984]])<ref name="age">In {{HM}}, Hagrid says Fang was "a puppy" in the [[1985–1986 school year]]. In the [[1984–1985 school year]], Fang can be seen on the school grounds as a little puppy picking up a stick and running down the hill towards Hagird's cabin. Dogs of the type reach their full size in about eighteen months, meaning Fang was born and acquired by Hagrid in 1984, before [[September]].</ref> was an over-sized [[boarhound]] [[dog]], and one of the [[Rubeus Hagrid's pets|pets]] under [[Rubeus Hagrid]]'s ownership and care.<ref name="PS8"/> A large dog, he lived with Hagrid in [[Hagrid's Hut|his hut]] and often accompanied him to places such as the [[Forbidden Forest]].<ref name="PS15"/> Fang was present for the majority of the [[Second Wizarding War]], such as the [[Battle of the Astronomy Tower]]<ref name="HBP28">{{HBP|B|28}}</ref> and the [[Battle of Hogwarts]].<ref name="DH31">{{DH|B|31}}</ref> He survived the war and was still alive and well in the late [[2000s]] and early [[2010s]].<ref name="MA"/>

==Biography==
===Early life===
{{Quote|Why don't you name him Fang? I've always liked that name for a dog.|A student recommended the name Fang|Harry Potter: Hogwarts Mystery}}
[[File:Fang pup1.png|250px|thumb|left|Fang as a little puppy, fetching a stick]]
Fang was born in around [[1984]], and became [[Rubeus Hagrid]]'s pet by [[September]] of the same year.<ref name="age"/> He was seen as a puppy on the school grounds fetching a stick and bolting down the hill back towards [[Hagrid's Hut]]. In [[1985]], Fang was trapped by the same [[Devil's Snare]] which Hagrid had rescued [[Jacob's sibling]] from the year before. Hagrid asked them if they could help him with the Devil's Snare the second time, being aware that using the [[Wand-Lighting Charm]] would only cause the dangerous plant to retreat further into the room in which it had been placed, placing Fang's life in danger.<ref name="HM2HH"/>

[[File:Hagrid with Fang and his flute.jpeg|250px|thumb|right|Fang relaxing outside his master's hut]]
Hagrid told Jacob's sibling to help him by brewing a [[Fire-Breathing Potion]]. Hagrid decided not to share what the potion was for, because he was embarrassed about his failure to keep a close enough eye on his pup and merely recited the ingredients. Jacob's sibling, [[Rowan Khanna]], [[Ben Copper]], and [[Penny Haywood]] eventually made the potion. Hagrid then told Jacob's sibling why he needed the potion, and they saved Fang from the Devil's Snare by using the potion. Hagrid then revealed he had not named the puppy yet, and they decide on the name Fang.<ref name="HM2HH">{{HM|2|Help Hagird!}}</ref>

===1980s===
At some point during the [[1985–1986 school year]], Fang became afraid of [[cat]]s, mostly due to [[Mrs Norris]]. Jacob's sibling, Rowan, Penny and [[Minerva McGonagall]] helped him overcome his fear and prepare for the [[pet gathering]].<ref name="SC">{{HM|2|Scaredy-Cats}}</ref>

{{Dialogue a-b|Jacob's sibling|You think Fang is brave...?|Rubeus Hagrid|Well, sometimes. When he's not sleepy. Or playful. At any rate, don't test him, alright?|Jacob's sibling and Hagrid discussing Fang in the [[1980s]]|Harry Potter: Hogwarts Mystery}}
During the [[1985–1986 school year]], Fang was kidnapped by [[Todd Cribb|Todd]] and [[Corrine Cribb]] along with many other pets as they wanted to get revenge on Hagrid for disrupting their poaching activities. They didn't know specifically which was Hagrid's pet but managed to capture Fang anyway (who was in the care of [[Merula Snyde]] at the time). When [[Jacob's sibling]] and [[Merula Snyde]] discovered Todd and Corrine Cribb, Fang came rushing to their side and was eventually returned to Hagrid.<ref name="HMP">{{HM|2|THE CASE OF THE MISSING PETS}}</ref> By September [[1986]], Fang enjoyed kipping in the [[Hogwarts Library|Library]] and hanging out in the [[Transfiguration (class)|Transfiguration]] [[Classroom 1B|Classroom]] because he saw a cat in there once, which was actually [[Minerva McGonagall]] in [[Animagus]] form.<ref name="Y3C1">{{HM|3|1}}</ref> At the beginning of the [[1986–1987 school year]], Fang went missing when he was scared by a [[fairy]] he found in the [[Rubeus Hagrid's pumpkin patch|pumpkin patch]] by Hagrid's Hut. Hagrid once again asked Jacob's sibling to help him. Hagrid then searched the [[Forbidden Forest]], telling them Fang once ran in there and couldn't find the way out.<ref name="Y3C1"/>

[[File:Wizard Fang HM720.png|250px|thumb|left|Fang disguised as a wizard]]
During the [[1990–1991 school year]], [[Jacob's sibling]] and their friends disguised Fang as a [[Wizardkind|wizard]] with a pointed wizard's hat and blue shirt, to bring him into [[St Mungo's Hospital for Magical Maladies and Injuries]] to visit a bedridden Hagrid, who had been missing him while hospitalised there. They lied to the hospital staff that Fang was a wizard who had been [[Transfiguration|transfigured]] into a dog sent in for treatment, so he could enter, as [[Creature|animals]] were not allowed inside the hospital.<ref name="HM720">{{HM|7|20}}</ref> Later that school year, Fang found [[Mrs Norris]] trapped in the roots of the [[Hogwarts Whomping Willow]].<ref name="HM746A">{{HM|7|46|Missing Mrs Norris}}</ref>

===1991-1995===
[[File:WB F1 Fang HarryMalfoyFangInForest 11428.jpg|250px|thumb|Fang in the Forbidden Forest with Harry Potter and Draco Malfoy]]
In [[1992]], Fang accompanied first-year students [[Draco Malfoy]] and [[Harry Potter]] into the [[Forbidden Forest]] for a detention, only to run away in fear after encountering a [[Tom Riddle|hooded figure]] drinking [[Unicorn blood|blood]] from a dead [[unicorn]]. After running away he soon found Hagrid, and [[Hermione Granger]], who immediately knew that Draco and Harry were in danger.<ref name="PS15">{{PS|B|15}}</ref> In [[1993]], Fang accompanied [[Ronald Weasley|Ron Weasley]] and Harry to visit [[Aragog]] in the [[Forbidden Forest]]. He, Harry, and Ron were nearly eaten by [[Forbidden Forest Acromantula colony|Aragog's children]], but they were rescued by the wild [[Flying Ford Anglia|Ford Anglia]] that was previously owned by Ron's father, [[Arthur Weasley]].<ref name="COS15">{{COS|B|15}}</ref>

[[File:B3C14M1 Buckbeak and Fang in Hagrid's Hut.jpg|250px|thumb|left|Fang and Buckbeak inside Hagrid's hut]]
Fang was present when [[Buckbeak]] was being reviewed by the [[British Ministry of Magic]]. He was seen sulking in his basket during one of the trio's many visits to Hagrid's hut during the [[1993–1994 school year]].<ref name="POA6">{{POA|B|6}}</ref><ref name="POA11">{{POA|B|11}}</ref> Fang also shared the hut with Buckbeak after Hagrid moved the hippogriff inside after [[Lucius Malfoy]] made his case to the [[Committee for the Disposal of Dangerous Creatures]] after Buckbeak attacked his son during a [[Care of Magical Creatures]] lesson that resulted in Draco's arm being injured.<ref name="POA21">{{POA|B|21}}</ref> In [[1994]], Hagrid decided not to take Fang with him to see the [[Dragon]]s kept in the Forbidden Forest with Harry, as he thought he would not like them.<ref name="GOF19">{{GOF|B|19}}</ref>

In [[1995]], when the trio tried to enter Hagrid's hut and Hagrid initialy did not answer due to being upset about [[Rita Skeeter]]'s article about him being a [[half-giant]], Fang barked and scratched at the door when they knocked. [[Albus Dumbledore]] who was with Hagrid let them in and Hagrid explained to them why he was feeling down.<ref name="GOF24">{{GOF|B|24}}</ref> Later that year, Fang went with Hagrid in order to look for [[Bartemius Crouch Senior]] in the Forbidden Forest, after [[Viktor Krum]] had been found [[Stunning Spell|stunned]].<ref name="GOF28">{{GOF|B|28}}</ref>

===Second Wizarding War===
In [[1996]], after Hagrid had returned to Hogwarts after his [[Mission to the Giant colony]], Fang was with him in the hut when the trio visited him to hear of his tale, and was very happy to see them. Fang also tried to lick [[Dolores Umbridge]]'s face when she entered, but she snapped at him to get away and waved her handbag at him.<ref name="OOTP20">{{OOTP|B|20}}</ref> When Hagrid was attacked by [[British Ministry of Magic|Ministry of Magic]] [[Three Aurors who tried to arrest Rubeus Hagrid|Aurors]] led by Dolores Umbridge, Fang was hit by a [[Stunning Spell]], when he tried to defend Hagrid, resulting in the responsible party being hurled over ten feet away by an enraged Hagrid. Hagrid took the stunned Fang with him when he escaped into the mountains.<ref name="OOTP31">{{OOTP|B|31}}</ref> After [[Tom Riddle|Voldemort]]'s return was made public and Umbridge was sacked, Hagrid and Fang returned to their hut at the edge of the Forbidden Forest.<ref name="OOTP38">{{OOTP|B|38}}</ref>

[[File:Halfblood-03201.jpg|250px|thumb|Fang next to [[Harry Potter]] after the funeral of Aragog]]
Fang was present during the funeral of Aragog "''sulking in his basket during the burial''" and afterwards, padded across the floor to them and laid his head in Harry Potter's lap and proceeded to slobber all over his robes.<ref name="HBP22">{{HBP|B|22}}</ref> Fang was also inside [[Hagrid's Hut]] when it was set ablaze by [[Death Eaters|Death Eater]] [[Thorfinn Rowle]], during the [[Battle of the Astronomy Tower]] on [[30 June]] [[1997]]. He was rescued shortly when Hagrid and Harry doused the fire with the [[Water-Making Spell]].<ref name="HBP28"/> It can be assumed that Fang was present at [[Funeral of Albus Dumbledore|Dumbledore's funeral]] with Hagrid.

In [[1998]], Fang went with Hagrid and [[Grawp]] to Hogwarts to help in the [[Battle of Hogwarts|defense of the castle]]. However, as soon as the fighting began Fang was startled when a vase nearby was hit by a [[spell]] and exploded, and he ran away in fright, with Hagrid going after him immediately.<ref name="DH31"/> He survived the battle and continued to live with Hagrid in his hut afterwards.<ref name="MA"/>

===21st century===
During the [[2009–2010 school year]], he went wild after hearing the songs of uncontrolled [[Fwooper]]s in [[Hagrid's Hut]]. When a [[Tiburon Merriweather's great-grandchild|student]] encountered him, he showed them some teeth before passing out.<ref name="MA">{{MA}}</ref>

==Physical description==
Fang was described as a giant [[boarhound]] with black fur.<ref name="PS8"/> He appeared to have {{W|Heterochromia iridum#In other animals|heterochromia}}, with his left eye being light blue and his right pupil orange.<ref name="eyes"/>

==Personality and traits==
{{Quote|<nowiki/>'Make yerselves at home,' said Hagrid, letting go of Fang, who bounded straight at Ron and started licking his ears. Like Hagrid, Fang was clearly not as fierce as he looked.|Fang's friendly personality|Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone}}
Fang was a large hound who slobbered constantly. On several occasions he completely soaked [[Harry Potter]]'s robes while laying his head on Harry's lap.<ref name="PS8"/> When someone entered Hagrid's hut, he would greet them with loud, booming barks<ref name="GOF24"/> and almost always licking their faces or ears.<ref name="OOTP20"/> He was very protective of Hagrid, but was a "bloody coward".<ref name="PSF">{{PS|F}}</ref> Fang was a very friendly, affectionate and sociable dog, and was often very happy to see the [[trio]] whenever they came to see Hagrid and him.<ref name="GOF24"/><ref name="GOF37">{{GOF|B|37}}</ref><ref name="OOTP20"/> He would also try to play with the other animals at Hogwarts, including [[Fawkes]], much to [[Albus Dumbledore]]'s amusement.<ref name="HMHHG">{{HM|6|HEAD BOYS AND GIRLS}}</ref>

Fang was very fond of taking baths, although he could only take them when he had the help of another person. Whenever he went too long without having a bath, he would start to smell of a [[Bundimun]] infestation.<ref name="HAH">{{HM|4|HAPPY ANNIVERSARY HOGWARTS}}</ref>

